Now white's queen is en prise, and his rook is forked too. But when the knight moved, it exposed a discovered attack against g2, threatening mate in 1. At this point, black expected white to play 22. Qf1 or 22. Qf3. Both moves stop the checkmate and save the white queen, but both moves also lose the rook at d1. Still, they're all that white has.
